_:e40e1a5e707acc79cf60bb602da36712 a <http://www.cidoc-crm.org/cidoc-crm/E52_Time-span> ;
	<http://www.cidoc-crm.org/cidoc-crm/P78_is_identified_by> "Before 1465 (9th/15th century)He was born and bred in the Berber tribe of Ǧazūla in Moroccan Sūs. Apart from his immense knowledge of Ṣūfism he was also a jurisconsult. He was  involved with the order of the Šāḏiliyya. After his retreat he went to live at Asfī (Safī) where he soon had so great a number of proselytes that the governor of the town felt obliged to expel him.\n               " .
